values:
&nbsp;So I don't know why, but I always feel like posting when I just have so many things going on in my head that I can't contain it.

1. I guess the first thing that I should write down is that I am dating Melissa. Melissa, in a word, is amazing. I think she is probably the most compatible person to me. Most of my past girlfriends have been a lot like me. I mean, have a lot of the same interests but thats the problem. As Jerry said in Seinfeld, "I cant date someone like me, I hate myself." I dont hate myself, but you know what I mean. It is nice to have a person around who does not simply agree with you all the time, or disagrees all the time, or makes you feel inadequate, or insensitive, or unwanted. She loves me for me. She doesnt just love the concept of a boyfriend, she actually genuinely loves me for who I am, and trust me, it is tough to love me. It may seem easy for the first few weeks, but it is like running a marathon.&nbsp;

2. Each semester brings new problems to the table. I have always gotten through semesters by saying something like "If I just get through this semester, next semester will be cake" Well folks, next semester is here, and I am failing Geology. Ok, im not failing, but I have a C-. That, in my book is close to failing, bc i dont get the GER for the class if I get a D. This wouldnt be a problem, but I have student teaching next semester, so I cannot fail, or I will have some serious issues next semester. And to be honest, this class and Sci of Nutrition have been the hardest classes for me. I dont get it. I did everything right! I checked ratemyprofessor, I asked around, I took an intro class, I took a class with the least amount of math, and it is AMAZINGLY hard. The professor is ridiculous! she teaches what you dont know, not necessarily what you do know. Its almost like its not an intro class at all. I just want the GER so I can go live my dreams, and they are crashing down around me if I get below a C in this class.&nbsp;

3. PSP. O PSP, I love you and hate you. I love you because of the friendships and how you help me get through the semester. Scott, Laura Cindy, Alyssa, Ryan, Jemma, yall are amazing...even though you cant read this. PSP, I hate you because I chose the wrong semester to take on soo much responsibilty. Hey, I love being Initiate Advisor, but this semeser, I am soo swamped that I cant put in the effort that I want to. It sucks. A lot.&nbsp;

4. Im tired, ill finish this later
